<subSubSection id="FA52B6552EDEFEB56F73A6AFBFFEB5E2" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="20E2F587A7BB93254508028B47AEBFC3" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C3F0925D701B5DEE5CA55389CABB227F" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName id="886179E021742839A90589649A0588AD" genus="I." lsidName="I. vallicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="vallicola">
<emphasis id="8E662C63ABD2BE44A6C7AE972E84DD2F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">I. vallicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="6E15161EEC076C49E41D732B979CFFAC" genus="I." lsidName="I. rigioclada" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="rigioclada">
<emphasis id="7049817D7D8240FB16776C26565C33A0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">I. rigioclada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Craib by sharing the procumbent habit, relatively small leaves and the similar flower shape, but it clearly differs from the latter by its usually 13-17-foliolate, flowers 3-5 mm long, calyx teeth triangular-lanceolate, and legumes 1-2 mm in diameter.
</paragraph>
<caption id="9BC249F78C06A8958391D826406E6119" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.199.85437.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691666" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
