<subSubSection id="965E131D24B5B17F828DECDD037675C2" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" type="phenology">
<paragraph id="0BCAE6B0837C84299A690FF3CD101080" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="27A252834B79AA9ACFBD494845877095" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Flowering occurs from September to November, fruiting from October to December.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="614CE1BE3886D2C9D3F095A8D9F99173" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F2C17BCECC3EF6504651E6D998537ABC" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B5402C46925FAB764A2DE37FD30170A3" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName id="FF21347CF2838A9E963A441CF780D102" authorityName="Huan C. Wang &amp; Jin L. Liu" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Indigofera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Indigofera vallicola" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vallicola">
<emphasis id="C73322393B5310B9F3D6202999239A72" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Indigofera vallicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to southwest China, where it has only been collected from two localities (ca. 45 km apart from each other) in central Yunnan to date: Xiao Luzhi (type locality) in Luzhijiang valley and Ainishan village in Shuangbai County. The climate in its habitat is seasonally hot and arid. In the type locality, 
<taxonomicName id="1528BA124988C3EDE8F4BAD33E8432F6" genus="I." lsidName="I. vallicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="vallicola">
<emphasis id="DF103D62EEC4FDBFC1B982C878E1627C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">I. vallicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the xerophilous scrubs or grasslands at elevations of 1200-1800 m, and its association include 
<taxonomicName id="64F72AAC1D7D24C00F5AF30388B54170" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Phyllanthaceae" genus="Phyllanthus" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Phyllanthus emblica" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="emblica">
<emphasis id="BBBE23C09AE67BE9843813E7CBB6E10C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Phyllanthus emblica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Linn. (
<taxonomicName id="80D60F6AFCA7E17EF930893DB62716BE" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Phyllanthaceae" genus="Phyllanthus" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Phyllanthaceae</taxonomicName>
