<subSubSection id="01121E2C4F9FF1245482EB58A4314B8F" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="571C5615692A6AAD99D475C3A0129416" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="960EF97F6B08C135EE34D2D160ABFD74" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">
The specific epithet is taken from the Latin &quot; 
<emphasis id="67C4EB3466BBBD68EEEB37428284B7C2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">vallis</emphasis>
&quot; (valley) and the suffix &quot;- 
<emphasis id="A172E102BB7593C1B96BD3641EC2BAA4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">cola</emphasis>
&quot; (dweller), referring to the habitat where the new species is found.
</paragraph>
