<subSubSection id="8593280BCCA89AA652E25ED25F48A66F" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph id="2A7361EBE4D99281EC214D0A32D1E6F2" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B2BF3BAEE17CA79B41FE3EB1D1DC881" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName id="1F2F215A514FCDA72F743A8CA078E917" authorityName="Huan C. Wang &amp; Jin L. Liu" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Indigofera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Indigofera vallicola" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vallicola">
<emphasis id="21150B50E2FB7DD9CF9424C9F40E77A1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Indigofera vallicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mainly characterized by having the prostrate habit, usually 13-17-foliolate leaves and relatively small (3-5 mm long) flowers. Morphologically, it is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="2EBBD0E8DE38DBF1D0E4D4B132062A08" genus="I." lsidName="I. rigioclada" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="rigioclada">
<emphasis id="5A6347014B5D7B1373D78A856C3F59E1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">I. rigioclada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Craib by sharing the procumbent habit, relatively small leaves and similar flower shape, but it clearly differs from the latter by its usually 13-17-foliolate (vs. 5-13-foliolate in 
<taxonomicName id="502847AA3B0923E2B647646AE5BF1FC2" genus="I." lsidName="I. rigioclada" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="rigioclada">
<emphasis id="A7D8E931A3FF142A75A81621E64AF4E5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">I. rigioclada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), flowers 3-5 mm (vs. 8-10 mm) long, calyx teeth triangular-lanceolate (vs. triangular), and legumes 1-2 mm (vs. larger than 2 mm) in diameter. 
<taxonomicName id="F4BEF89689DED7D7D31389517F365B4A" authorityName="Huan C. Wang &amp; Jin L. Liu" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Indigofera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Indigofera vallicola" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vallicola">
<emphasis id="70359BA898B9D0C9AA8CFC539C2BB44C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Indigofera vallicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also more or less similar to 
<taxonomicName id="0692EF9C185EFB70B034BF874B729794" genus="I." lsidName="I. henryi" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="henryi">
<emphasis id="C4B30F53FE70ECB0B041C3BBB1AF366E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">I. henryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Franch. in its overall appearance, relatively gracile pedicels and shape of calyx. Nevertheless, 
<taxonomicName id="D105698E7DBC29CB222D44C5D59261E0" genus="I." lsidName="I. henryi" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="henryi">
<emphasis id="DC3E8FEFA1DEDFBCA19C21B3E5D71281" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">I. henryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly differs from the former in having the linear stipules usually 5 mm long (vs. lanceolate to subulate, 1-2 mm long in 
<taxonomicName id="AE3C4D1B85C9A4D0142BEE6B387B9B1D" genus="I." lsidName="I. vallicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="vallicola">
<emphasis id="B3B158C0435C0EE5405FA823414B57B8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">I. vallicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), leaves larger, 3-10 cm (vs. 2-5 cm) long, rachis of adaxially flattened, slightly winged (vs. grooved and without winged), leaflet blades 1.7-2.3 
<normalizedToken id="EB40B40E97F45E8A164230EB6EA23804" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-1.2 cm (vs. 0.2-1.2 
<normalizedToken id="5A0CA8FEB30A381A6AF4AD2F6FCF9F1E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.15-0.5 cm), pedicels (2)3-6(-9) mm (vs. 1-2 mm) long, corolla much larger in size, white (vs. pink), with 7-9 
<normalizedToken id="35262B50D42F65EF4919141B3041B91C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-6 mm (vs. 3-5 
<normalizedToken id="7179411EC7928C476C19FE7840D25D8A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 mm) standard and 7-9 mm (vs. 3-5 mm) long keels.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="530D2A3E3FAD26421416C45241BD4568" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName id="F21121A22206DF5452697B3E015147DD" authorityName="Huan C. Wang &amp; Jin L. Liu" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Indigofera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Indigofera vallicola" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vallicola">
<emphasis id="F99A04BC68F62D6CE82570988D83524A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Indigofera vallicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is somewhat close to 
<taxonomicName id="3798DF29543A999B765ECE8DA014AB1A" genus="I." lsidName="I. franchetii" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="franchetii">
<emphasis id="C73739A8D16524D3EBEF9636F81777DB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">I. franchetii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
X. F. Gao &amp; Schrire, an endemic species found from the dry-hot valleys of Jinsha River and its tributaries in southwestern China. Nevertheless, 
<taxonomicName id="448233C44FB09E97FA239B339C82BFE7" genus="I." lsidName="I. franchetii" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="franchetii">
<emphasis id="E060EFC32CEE76C7635CEA0ECE69EA19" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">I. franchetii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="B632EA75CE858B0A5CA8E969078E0A07" genus="I." lsidName="I. vallicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="vallicola">
<emphasis id="850C8294CC2CCCD5A75250DE5F165A82" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">I. vallicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having 35-50 cm long branchlets, (11-)17-27-foliolate leaves ca. 5-10 cm long, racemes 5.5-11 cm long, peduncles 0.7-3.0 cm long, pedicels 0.5-1.0 mm long, calyces cup-shaped, standards oblong-elliptic, 7-8 mm long, legumes 2.5-4.0 cm long, 1.5-2.5 mm in diameter. The new species shows some similarities with 
<taxonomicName id="6E998177A3A82B3C2D5709D81D72A356" genus="I." lsidName="I. chaetodonta" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="chaetodonta">
<emphasis id="725A03364E858A99D9E71463D3D58C2F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">I. chaetodonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Franch. in the habit, flower size, and calyx shape. However, 
<taxonomicName id="94ED956E4B2C667E1E7341EB50A01D6C" genus="I." lsidName="I. chaetodonta" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="chaetodonta">
<emphasis id="AE067748DB371301AF79DF74B11D6B34" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">I. chaetodonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is well differentiated from 
<taxonomicName id="7B64CD9A678C13AF4C71092111A4DC3F" genus="I." lsidName="I. vallicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="vallicola">
<emphasis id="96E778E1A75CD68CCCCA2B0C72CE7D02" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">I. vallicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having (5 or) 7- or 9-foliolate leaves 0.6-1.5 (-2.0) cm long, leaflet blades oblong to oblanceolate, 3.5-6 
<normalizedToken id="C02B8E83252B9C87DD03606B0E33D291" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-2.5 mm, adaxially nearly glabrous, standards broadly elliptic, 5-7 
<normalizedToken id="7AE48A491CD3DFC1A41F6BD321F645BA" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
ca. 4 mm, legumes 1.5-2.0 cm long, glabrous or with sparse appressed medifixed trichomes.
</paragraph>
